.TH "sprd_mcdt_chan_read" 9 "sprd_mcdt_chan_read" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
sprd_mcdt_chan_read \- read data from the MCDT channel's fifo
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" sprd_mcdt_chan_read
.BI "(struct sprd_mcdt_chan *chan "  ","
.BI "char *rx_buf "  ","
.BI "u32 size "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "chan" 12
the MCDT channel
.IP "rx_buf" 12
receive buffer
.IP "size" 12
data size
.SH "NOTE"
We can not read data from the channel fifo when enabling the DMA mode,
otherwise the reading data will be invalid.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Usually user need start to read data once receiving the fifo full interrupt.

Returns data size of reading successfully, or an error code on failure.
